    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but \"the general good\" is usually defined by the majority or the state. if a religious group's belief is fundamentally at odds with modern human rights or scientific consensus, shouldn't the state's obligation to progress and equality automatically override their \"moral beliefs\"? like, at what point does religious freedom just become an excuse to hold back social progress or deny rights to others?",
